  <title type="text">Learning Racket via some Pollen</title>
  <link rel="alternate" href="https://brittAnderson.github.io/2021/05/learning-racket-via-some-pollen.html?utm_source=raisin&amp;utm_medium=Atom" />
  <id>urn:https-brittAnderson-github-io:-2021-05-learning-racket-via-some-pollen-html</id>
  <published>2021-05-26T20:21:50Z</published>
  <updated>2021-05-26T20:21:50Z</updated>
  <author>
   <name>Britt Anderson</name></author>
  <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;Learning a new programming language has two characteristic early stages: the tutorial stage where everything is scripted and goes well; and the stage where you first try to do something yourself and it all gets much more real. This entry records some of my impressions on this process as regards &lt;a href="https://racket-lang.org/"&gt;racket&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="https://docs.racket-lang.org/pollen/"&gt;pollen&lt;/a&gt;. Can I turn the children&amp;rsquo;s story I wrote for my wife into a series of web pages?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;a href="https://brittAnderson.github.io/2021/05/learning-racket-via-some-pollen.html?utm_source=raisin&amp;amp;utm_medium=Atom"&gt;&lt;em&gt;More&amp;hellip;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</content></entry>
